text: Yesterday I bought 3 scratch tickets. The one I bought for $1 won me $5. The one I bought for $2 won me $5, and the other one I bought for $2 won me a free ticket. :money_mouth_face:
Confession: I don't enjoy doing scratch-its but have been given them for several holidays by random people. I've never won a single time.
I did not enjoy them even before my streak of never winning
Confession: My brother bought me my first scratch card when I was 6 years old. I won $25 and have never been the same
Confession: I bought one scratch ticket on my 18th birthday (& a swisher sweet), won back the $2 I spent on it and haven't "gambled" since then
I won $980 on a slot machine once then a few weeks later won $250, and i dont normally play those things
another confession but unrelated: i want to leave every channel
confession: you can buy scratchers in CA at 18 (not AZ tho, where I born'd + raise'd) ... and it seemed like such a big + fancy thing when I did it.
